@jonathan-hurley I did fetch and merge the feature branch, I think these extra commits come from the merge, do you know any other rebase git commands I should run? Fortunately there is no extra code there. Thanks.

@scottduan Only *before* you open the pull request:

```
git rebase upstream/branch-feature-AMBARI-14714
```

Once the PR is open, please avoid rebasing or amending commits that are already pushed to the PR, because they alter history.  Usually you don't need to merge either, unless there are conflicts which you must resolve.  Incremental commits to address review items should be fine.
